GROUP F — APN Mismatch Double fsMutex Deadlock (Issue 32)
gprs_helpers.ino:107–108 / gprs.ino:3640, 3652, 3669
start_gprs() is called while modemMutex is held (line 387). Inside, load_apn_config() takes fsMutex. On APN mismatch, fsMutex is released. Then save_apn_config() immediately re-takes fsMutex. Since FreeRTOS mutexes are non-recursive, the second take succeeds (the mutex was released). The deadlock risk is actually subtler than previously described: if a context switch to another task (e.g., lcdkeypad) occurs between the fsMutex release and the save_apn_config() take, and that other task takes and holds fsMutex, the GPRS task blocks inside save_apn_config() while holding modemMutex. Any task needing modemMutex then starves. Fix: restructure start_gprs() to collect the APN to save, release modemMutex first, then call save_apn_config().

